      About this item

      • [3 Straps Included] DEKEELIFE smart watches for women comes with 3 bands - one gold stainless steel strap, one pink silicone strap and one white silicone strap. Wear different colors and materials of the strap to switch between different styles. The smartwatch fits any band with a width of 22mm.
      • [24/7 Health Monitoring] The heart rate monitor watch supports real-time monitoring. The smart watch with blood pressure monitor, sleep (deep sleep/light sleep) monitor, and women's health function, etc. Supports synchronization of data to APP for easy viewing.
      • [Make Calls and Receive Messages] The smart watch uses Bluetooth 5.3 technology to ensure a faster and more stable connection. Answer/make calls, receive messages and APP notifications through the watch. Note: Smart watches ONLY suppot receive message, can't reply to messages.
      • [Smart Watch for Android Phones/iPhones] The smartwatch is compatible with most iPhones and Android phones (Android 6.0 and above/IOS9.0 and above). The smart watch for women supports synchronization of 100 contacts, weather forecast, play music, control camera and more. Please make sure your phone is paired with the watch before use.
      • [110+ Sport Modes Fitness Tracker] The Fitness watches for women/men supports 110+ sports modes. Accurately record heart rate, steps, distance, calories burned. The activity tracker is able to realize GPS location through your phone and clearly upload your movement path.
      • [IP68 Waterproof Fitness Watch] IP68 waterproof sport watch easily copes with indoor/outdoor rainy day sports. No need to take off the watch while washing hands. Note: Don't wear smartwatches while bathing, Don't press the buttons while swimming.
      • [Professional After-sales Service] DEKELIFE is committed to providing high quality products to our customers. If you encounter any problems during use. We will provide professional customer service support.

      • Why can't smartwatches record steps?

        Before using the step tracking feature, please shake the watch to allow it to sense vibrations and initiate step counting.

      • Does the smart watch compatible with iOS phones or Android phones? Why can't my watch receive text messages?

        This smart watch is compatible with both Android/iOS phones. First, confirm that smart phone can receive and display text messages, turn on all message notifications in the APP. After setup is complete, try pairing the watch again.

      • Does this watch have a blood pressure function?

        Yes, This fitness watch not only monitors blood pressure, but also adds new functions such as menstruation recording.

      • How long can it be used on a single charge?

        3 days for daily use. Charging time is about 2 hours.

      • What should I do if I don’t know how to use the product or if the product is defective?

        We have a professional service team to solve your problems. They will help you (via Amazon Order Number)!

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      Amazon Customer
      4 out of 5 stars
      Good watch for price
      The watch face is a little bit larger than I would like. It feels clunky on my wrist. With that being said, I love everything else about it. It appears pretty accurate with my PO2 levels, heart rate and BP. It's nice seeing my sleep hours and makes realize I'm not sleeping as soundly as I thought. I have used the phone feature, but probably won't use it often. Voices sound very distant. Watch was easy to set up, although the instructions could be larger. Downloading the app was also very easy. Watch holds a charge for a week, depending how much you play with it. Watch came with 3 interchangeable bands and an extra set of stems. I've previously had several Fitbits and this is actually better.

      • Ankitha
        5.0 out of 5 stars As Good as it Gets - Bought it for BP Measuring
        Reviewed in the United States on October 1, 2024
        Color: SilverVerified Purchase
        The media could not be loaded.
        Out of the Box: Nice minimalist packaging, less trash. Options on the three bands , all are comfortable and good match for a variety wardrobe. The two extra pins for extra wrist-bands, super idea. . Installing the app software and linking the watch was a breeze, however there were paid app installation offers during the process. The app is nothing to write home about, functional and meets the needs.

        Charging the watch: The charging cable is non-standard. Attaches to the watch with magnetic mechanism. Right out of the box, the watch was 90% charged, when connected to a standard 2.4A USB charger (not provided with the watch) it got up to 99% in less than 12 minutes. That is very par with competitive watches with similar features. Later, after three days of regular use, the watch was down to 80% and charged up to 99% in about 20 minutes.

        General Features: Loved the variety and selection of faces for the watch. And it lets you customize on your own also. .
        Most offered features are similar to competitive watches, checked out most of them and they are just fine. Nothing was lacking for daily normal usage. All metrics were as accurate as my previous watch, I wore them both for two days to just get a comparison.

        Blood Pressure: The key feature that interested me was the blood pressure reading. The seller representative cautioned that this is extrapolated data and may not be suitable for clinical purposes. My need is for an occasional check in a day for any abnormal reading – for which this watch meets the need well. I compared the reading with a cuff-blood pressure reader for calibration (see video). Took a couple of readings together, and then separately spacing each reading by several minutes. The DIA reading seemed to give a higher value everytime, the SYS was fairly close. My previous watch had a calibration in settings with which I could get close to the machine reading. Overall, serves the purpose. .

        Wishlist: The charging cable and contacts are less than intuitive – it is polarized (see video). Perhaps an improved design would have a better attach mechanism.
        There is no storage case for the parts for later use – the wrist bands, the pins and instructions. Perhaps a small storage bag would be a great inclusion (see picture)
